<div dir="ltr"><div><br></div><div><font face="monospace, monospace">       INTEGER JEFF(3)</font></div><div><font face="monospace, monospace">       DATA JEFF/4HMR. ,4HFORT,3HRAN/</font></div><div><br></div><div>If you can understand that, you should probably pretend you can&#39;t :-)</div><div><br></div><div>-Paul [who has actually used Computed GO TO and Arithmetic IF]</div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Fri, Feb 20, 2015 at 11:28 AM, Larry Baker <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:baker@usgs.gov" target="_blank">baker@usgs.gov</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex"><div style="word-wrap:break-word">Excellent, Mr. Fortran.  Thank you.<div><br></div><div>By the way, I meant to write Branch ON Low Bit Set/Clear.<div><br></div><div>
